Part of Speech: adjective
Definition: 	1. {'short': 'spontaneously violent'}
	2. {'long': 'acting or done quickly and without thought, often resulting in unrestrained behavior.'}
Synonyms: unthinking, impulsive
Antonyms: deliberate, restrained

Part of Speech: verb
Definition: 	1. {'main': 'to emit or give off an odor, feeling of smell.'}
	2. {'subordinate': 'To produce sound naturally without apparent effort; flow forth spontaneously and smoothly'}
Synonyms: emanates, emits, exudes
Antonyms: absorbs, releases into the air or environment without effort from within, conceals

Part of Speech: adverb
Definition: 	1. {'description': 'to an eminent degree; very'}
	2. {'definition': 'without difficulty or effort.'}
Synonyms: undoubtedly, no doubt
Antonyms: unmistakably not, clearly unworthy

Part of Speech: adjective
Definition: 	1. {'definition': 'performed or conducted with stringent accuracy and completeness.'}
	2. {'definition': 'demanding in requirement of care, orderliness, punctuality; severely strict'}
Synonyms: stringent, exacting, meticulous
Antonyms: lax, negligible

Part of Speech: verb
Definition: 	1. {'definition1': 'to drive forward or onward.'}
	2. {'definition2': 'to make (a machine, rocket, etc.) move.'}
Synonyms: push, drive forward
Antonyms: drag, pull backward
